tafsir[15]{c,v,t}:
  82,1,"When the sky will split apart because of the angels descending from it."
  82,2,"When the stars fall one after the other and are scattered."
  82,3,"When the seas are opened into one another and they merge."
  82,4,"When the soil of graves is turned over to resurrect the dead in them."
  82,10,"Over you are angels who record your deeds."
  82,12,"They know of every action you do and they write it down."
  82,13,"Those who do abundant acts of good and obedience will be in everlasting bliss on the day of judgment."
  82,14,"Those who committed iniquity will be in a fire that will be burned over them."
  82,15,"They will enter it on the day of recompense and suffer from its heat."
  82,16,"They will never be absent from it. Instead they will remain in it forever."
  82,17,"O Messenger! What will tell you what the day of justice is?"
  83,1,"Destruction and loss be for those who give short measure."
  83,3,"But when they measure or weigh for people they reduce the measurement and weight. This was the practice of the people of Madinah at the time the Prophet (peace be on him) migrated to them."
  83,4,"Do these people who do this evil act not know that they will resurrected before Allah?!"
  83,5,"For the reckoning and recompense on a day that is great because of the trials and horrors it contains."